<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>EFL Game Templates</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@700;900&family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root{--bg:#0a0a0f;--card:#1a1a24;--border:#2a2a3a;--accent:#f0c040;--accent2:#5ee7b0;--accent3:#f07070;--text:#e8e8f0;--muted:#7777aa;--code-bg:#0d0d14;}
*,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0;}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth;}
body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:300;line-height:1.6;min-height:100vh;}
header{position:sticky;top:0;z-index:100;background:rgba(10,10,15,.96);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:0 32px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;height:60px;}
.site-title{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);white-space:nowrap;}
.nav-pills{display:flex;gap:4px;overflow-x:auto;flex:1;}
.np{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:3px;color:var(--muted);text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;border:1px solid transparent;transition:all .2s;}
.np:hover{background:var(--card);color:var(--text);border-color:var(--border);}
.np.active{background:var(--accent);color:var(--bg);}
.lang-toggle{display:flex;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden;flex-shrink:0;}
.lb{padding:4px 12px;background:transparent;border:none;color:var(--muted);font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;}
.lb.active{background:var(--accent);color:var(--bg);}
main{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:48px 32px 100px;}
.intro{margin-bottom:60px;text-align:center;}
.intro h1{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:900;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:12px;}
.intro h1 em{color:var(--accent);font-style:normal;}
.intro p{color:var(--muted);max-width:560px;margin:0 auto;}
.gs{margin-bottom:80px;scroll-margin-top:70px;}
.gh{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:24px;padding-bottom:16px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
.ge{font-size:2.4rem;line-height:1;}
.gtb h2{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:clamp(1.4rem,2.5vw,1.9rem);font-weight:700;margin-bottom:5px;}
.gtb p{color:var(--muted);font-size:.88rem;}
.tags{display:flex;gap:5px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:7px;}
.tag{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:2px 9px;border-radius:2px;background:var(--bg);color:var(--muted);border:1px solid var(--border);}
.tag.sk{background:#0f1e14;color:var(--accent2);border-color:#1a3020;}
.tag.lv{background:#1e0f0f;color:var(--accent3);border-color:#3a1a1a;}
.tab-bar{display:flex;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);gap:0;}
.tb{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:9px 18px;background:transparent;border:none;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;color:var(--muted);cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;margin-bottom:-1px;}
.tb.on{color:var(--accent);border-bottom-color:var(--accent);}
.tab-panel{display:none;}
.tab-panel.on{display:block;}
.prev-wrap{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:none;border-radius:0 0 8px 8px;overflow:hidden;}
.prev-bar{background:var(--bg);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:7px 14px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;}
.tl-row{display:flex;gap:5px;}
.tl{width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;}
.prev-url{flex:1;background:rgba(255,255,255,.04);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:3px;padding:3px 9px;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:var(--muted);}
.prev-cnt{position:relative;width:100%;height:460px;}
.prev-cnt iframe{width:100%;height:100%;border:none;display:block;}
.open-btn{position:absolute;bottom:10px;right:10px;background:var(--accent);color:var(--bg);font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.07em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:5px 12px;border-radius:3px;border:none;cursor:pointer;font-weight:500;}
.code-panel{background:var(--code-bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:none;border-radius:0 0 8px 8px;}
.code-hdr{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:9px 14px;background:var(--card);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
.code-lang{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent2);}
.copy-btn{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.07em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:4px 11px;background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:3px;color:var(--muted);cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;}
.copy-btn:hover{background:var(--accent);color:var(--bg);border-color:var(--accent);}
.code-scroll{max-height:400px;overflow-y:auto;overflow-x:auto;padding:18px 22px;}
.code-scroll pre{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:.77rem;line-height:1.7;color:#c0cce0;white-space:pre;}
.cbox{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:none;border-radius:0 0 8px 8px;padding:22px;}
.cbox h3{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent2);margin-bottom:14px;}
.cgrid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:10px;}
@media(max-width:600px){.cgrid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.prev-cnt{height:340px;}}
.citem{background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:12px;}
.cik{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.07em;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:3px;}
.civ{color:var(--muted);font-size:.82rem;}
@media(max-width:580px){header{padding:0 12px;}main{padding:32px 14px 80px;}}
::-webkit-scrollbar{width:5px;height:5px;}
::-webkit-scrollbar-track{background:var(--bg);}
::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb{background:var(--border);border-radius:3px;}
.how-to{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0d1a10,#0a1208);border:1px solid #1e3a20;border-radius:12px;padding:24px 28px;margin-bottom:60px;max-width:780px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;}
.how-to h2{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.3rem;color:var(--accent2);margin-bottom:12px;}
.how-to ol{padding-left:20px;color:var(--muted);font-size:.88rem;line-height:2;}
.how-to ol li{margin-bottom:4px;}
.how-to ol li strong{color:var(--text);}
.how-to .tip{margin-top:14px;background:rgba(240,192,64,.07);border:1px solid rgba(240,192,64,.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;font-size:.82rem;color:var(--accent);}
.dl-btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;background:var(--accent2);color:var(--bg);font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:8px 16px;border-radius:5px;border:none;cursor:pointer;font-weight:500;margin-top:14px;transition:opacity .2s;}
.dl-btn:hover{opacity:.85;}
.claude-prompt{background:#050508;border:1px solid #1a1a2e;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;margin-top:10px;}
.claude-prompt-label{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#7070c0;margin-bottom:8px;}
.claude-prompt-text{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:.75rem;color:#b0c0e0;line-height:1.6;white-space:pre-wrap;}
.copy-prompt-btn{font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.07em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:4px 11px;background:var(--bg);border:1px solid #2a2a5a;border-radius:3px;color:#7070c0;cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;margin-top:8px;display:inline-block;}
.copy-prompt-btn:hover{background:#2a2a5a;color:#c0c0ff;}
.teacher-note{background:#0d0d16;border-left:3px solid var(--accent);padding:10px 14px;border-radius:0 6px 6px 0;font-size:.8rem;color:var(--muted);margin-top:10px;line-height:1.5;}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <div class="site-title" data-en="EFL Game Templates" data-es="Plantillas de Juegos EFL">EFL Game Templates</div>
  <nav class="nav-pills">
    <a class="np" href="#pp" data-en="Pasapalabra" data-es="Pasapalabra">Pasapalabra</a>
    <a class="np" href="#mm" data-en="Millionaire" data-es="Millonario">Millionaire</a>
    <a class="np" href="#jj" data-en="Jeopardy" data-es="Jeopardy">Jeopardy</a>
    <a class="np" href="#tb" data-en="Taboo" data-es="Taboo">Taboo</a>
    <a class="np" href="#cl" data-en="Cluedo" data-es="Cluedo">Cluedo</a>
    <a class="np" href="#er" data-en="Escape Room" data-es="Sala de Escape">Escape Room</a>
    <a class="np" href="#im" data-en="Imposter" data-es="Impostor">Imposter</a>
    <a class="np" href="#sq" data-en="Squares" data-es="Cuadrados">Squares</a>
  </nav>
  <div class="lang-toggle">
    <button class="lb active" onclick="setLang('en')" id="btn-en">EN</button>
    <button class="lb" onclick="setLang('es')" id="btn-es">ES</button>
  </div>
</header>
<main>
  <div class="intro">
    <h1 data-en="EFL Game <em>Templates</em>" data-es="Plantillas de <em>Juegos EFL</em>">EFL Game <em>Templates</em></h1>
    <p data-en="Seven fully playable HTML games — live preview, copy code, and customisation guide for each." data-es="Siete juegos HTML completamente funcionales — vista previa en vivo, código copiable y guía de personalización para cada uno.">Seven fully playable HTML games — live preview, copy code, and customisation guide for each.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="how-to">
    <h2>📖 How to use this guide</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Browse</strong> each game below using the navigation bar at the top.</li>
      <li><strong>Live Preview</strong> — click to play the game directly in this page and test it works.</li>
      <li><strong>HTML Code</strong> — click "Copy Full Code", then open a <em>new blank file</em> in Notepad (Windows) or TextEdit (Mac), paste the code, and save it as <code>game.html</code>. Open that file in any browser.</li>
      <li><strong>Customise</strong> — read the guide and use the ready-made Claude prompts to generate your own content in seconds. Paste Claude's output back into the code where indicated.</li>
      <li><strong>Download</strong> — use the download button on any game to save that game's file directly.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="tip">💡 <strong>Tip:</strong> You don't need to know how to code. Each game is a single self-contained file. Copy → Paste → Save → Open. That's it.</div>
  </div>

  <section class="gs" id="pp">
    <div class="gh">
      <div class="ge">🔵</div>
      <div class="gtb">
        <h2>Pasapalabra</h2>
        <p>Animated rosco — one definition per letter, timed, with skip mechanics.</p>
        <div class="tags"><span class="tag sk">Vocabulary</span><span class="tag sk">Listening</span><span class="tag lv">A2–C2</span><span class="tag ">Individual / Teams</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-bar">
      <button class="tb on" onclick="sw('pp','prev',this)">Live Preview</button>
      <button class="tb" onclick="sw('pp','code',this)">HTML Code</button>
      <button class="tb" onclick="sw('pp','cust',this)">Customise</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel on" id="pp-prev">
      <div class="prev-wrap">
        <div class="prev-bar">
          <div class="tl-row"><div class="tl" style="background:#ff5f57"></div><div class="tl" style="background:#ffbd2e"></div><div class="tl" style="background:#28ca42"></div></div>
          <div class="prev-url">pasapalabra_template.html</div>
        </div>
        <div class="prev-cnt">
          <iframe id="pp-frame" title="Pasapalabra" src="about:blank"></iframe>
          <button class="open-btn" onclick="openFull('pp')">Open Full Screen</button>
          <button class="open-btn" style="right:160px;background:var(--accent2);" onclick="downloadGame('pp')">⬇ Download</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="pp-code">
      <div class="code-panel">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <span class="code-lang">HTML + CSS + JavaScript</span>
          <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode('pp', this)">Copy Full Code</button>
        </div>
        <div class="code-scroll"><pre id="pp-codepre">Loading...</pre></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="pp-cust">
      <div class="cbox">
        <h3>What to customise</h3>
        <div class="cgrid">
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">gameData[ ] — the questions</div><div class="civ">25 clue objects. Each needs: letter, condition (STARTS WITH / CONTAINS X), question, answer. Use the Claude prompt below to generate a full set.</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">Multiple answers</div><div class="civ">Set <code>answer</code> to an array: <code>["Recall","Remind"]</code>. The game accepts any of them as correct.</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">Time limit</div><div class="civ">In the code, find the <code>&lt;select id="tsel"&gt;</code> element. Add <code>selected</code> to whichever option you want as default (2 min, 3 min, 5 min, or no limit).</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">Skip mechanic</div><div class="civ">"Pasapalabra" button pauses the clock — authentic to the TV format. Students skip and come back to hard letters at the end.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="teacher-note">🎯 <strong>How to use in class:</strong> Individual or pairs. Display on projector. Student answers aloud or types. Works great as a warm-up or revision activity. The ring fills with green as correct answers accumulate — very motivating!</div>
        <div class="claude-prompt">
          <div class="claude-prompt-label">📋 Ready-to-use Claude prompt — copy and paste this into Claude</div>
          <div class="claude-prompt-text" id="pp-prompt">Generate a Pasapalabra gameData array in JavaScript for EFL students at [B1/B2] level on the topic of [e.g. technology / crime / emotions].

For each of the 26 letters A–Z, write one clue object like this:
{letter:'A', condition:'STARTS WITH A', question:'Definition or clue here.', answer:'Answer'}

Rules:
- The answer must start with (or contain) the letter shown
- For K, Q, X, Y, Z use condition:'CONTAINS K' etc. if needed
- Keep questions short and clear (max 15 words)
- For multiple valid answers use: answer:['Word1','Word2']
- Level: [B1/B2], Topic: [YOUR TOPIC]

Output only the JavaScript array, no explanation.</div>
          <button class="copy-prompt-btn" onclick="copyPrompt('pp-prompt',this)">Copy Prompt</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="gs" id="mm">
    <div class="gh">
      <div class="ge">💰</div>
      <div class="gtb">
        <h2>Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?</h2>
        <p>Progressive 4-choice questions with 50:50, Phone a Friend, and Ask the Audience lifelines.</p>
        <div class="tags"><span class="tag sk">Listening</span><span class="tag sk">Reading</span><span class="tag lv">A1–C2</span><span class="tag ">Individual / Pairs</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-bar">
      <button class="tb on" onclick="sw('mm','prev',this)">Live Preview</button>
      <button class="tb" onclick="sw('mm','code',this)">HTML Code</button>
      <button class="tb" onclick="sw('mm','cust',this)">Customise</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel on" id="mm-prev">
      <div class="prev-wrap">
        <div class="prev-bar">
          <div class="tl-row"><div class="tl" style="background:#ff5f57"></div><div class="tl" style="background:#ffbd2e"></div><div class="tl" style="background:#28ca42"></div></div>
          <div class="prev-url">millionaire_template.html</div>
        </div>
        <div class="prev-cnt">
          <iframe id="mm-frame" title="Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?" src="about:blank"></iframe>
          <button class="open-btn" onclick="openFull('mm')">Open Full Screen</button>
          <button class="open-btn" style="right:160px;background:var(--accent2);" onclick="downloadGame('mm')">⬇ Download</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="mm-code">
      <div class="code-panel">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <span class="code-lang">HTML + CSS + JavaScript</span>
          <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode('mm', this)">Copy Full Code</button>
        </div>
        <div class="code-scroll"><pre id="mm-codepre">Loading...</pre></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="mm-cust">
      <div class="cbox">
        <h3>What to customise</h3>
        <div class="cgrid">
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">questions[ ] — the quiz</div><div class="civ">12 questions. Each needs: <code>q</code> (question text), <code>a b c d</code> (four options), <code>correct</code> (the letter of the right answer). Use the Claude prompt below.</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">prizes[ ]</div><div class="civ">12 prize labels shown on screen. Change <code>"1,000,000"</code> to <code>"100 points"</code> or class-specific rewards if you prefer.</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">Lifelines</div><div class="civ">50:50, Phone a Friend, and Ask the Audience are all built in. Students love using them — it creates great speaking opportunities.</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">Safe havens (var safe)</div><div class="civ">Currently set to questions 5 and 9. If a student answers wrong, they keep their last safe haven prize. Change the numbers in <code>var safe=[4,8]</code> (0-indexed).</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="teacher-note">🎯 <strong>How to use in class:</strong> Project on screen. One student or team at a time answers. Other students can be the "audience" for the Ask the Audience lifeline — they discuss and vote. Great for grammar review or reading comprehension.</div>
        <div class="claude-prompt">
          <div class="claude-prompt-label">📋 Ready-to-use Claude prompt — copy and paste this into Claude</div>
          <div class="claude-prompt-text" id="mm-prompt">Generate a JavaScript questions array for a Who Wants to Be a Millionaire EFL game.

12 questions, increasing difficulty. Topic: [e.g. reported speech / British culture / collocations]. Level: [A2/B1/B2/C1].

Format each like this:
{q:"Question text here?", a:"Option A", b:"Option B", c:"Option C", d:"Option D", correct:"b"}

Rules:
- correct must be "a", "b", "c", or "d"
- Questions 1–4: easy. 5–8: medium. 9–12: hard
- All options should be plausible (no obviously wrong distractors)
- Output only the JavaScript array, no explanation</div>
          <button class="copy-prompt-btn" onclick="copyPrompt('mm-prompt',this)">Copy Prompt</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="gs" id="jj">
    <div class="gh">
      <div class="ge">📺</div>
      <div class="gtb">
        <h2>Jeopardy!</h2>
        <p>Clickable board — 5 categories × 5 point values. Answer in the form of a question.</p>
        <div class="tags"><span class="tag sk">Reading</span><span class="tag sk">Speaking</span><span class="tag lv">A2–C1</span><span class="tag ">Teams / Class</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-bar">
      <button class="tb on" onclick="sw('jj','prev',this)">Live Preview</button>
      <button class="tb" onclick="sw('jj','code',this)">HTML Code</button>
      <button class="tb" onclick="sw('jj','cust',this)">Customise</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel on" id="jj-prev">
      <div class="prev-wrap">
        <div class="prev-bar">
          <div class="tl-row"><div class="tl" style="background:#ff5f57"></div><div class="tl" style="background:#ffbd2e"></div><div class="tl" style="background:#28ca42"></div></div>
          <div class="prev-url">jeopardy_template.html</div>
        </div>
        <div class="prev-cnt">
          <iframe id="jj-frame" title="Jeopardy!" src="about:blank"></iframe>
          <button class="open-btn" onclick="openFull('jj')">Open Full Screen</button>
          <button class="open-btn" style="right:160px;background:var(--accent2);" onclick="downloadGame('jj')">⬇ Download</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="jj-code">
      <div class="code-panel">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <span class="code-lang">HTML + CSS + JavaScript</span>
          <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode('jj', this)">Copy Full Code</button>
        </div>
        <div class="code-scroll"><pre id="jj-codepre">Loading...</pre></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="jj-cust">
      <div class="cbox">
        <h3>What to customise</h3>
        <div class="cgrid">
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">cats[ ] — category names</div><div class="civ">5 category names shown at the top of the board. Keep them short (max 3 words) so they fit in the grid. Example: "Irregular Verbs", "Phrasal Verbs".</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">clues[ ][ ] — the board</div><div class="civ">25 clue objects: 5 categories × 5 point values (100–500). Each: <code>{q:"Clue here", a:"What is the answer?"}</code>. Answers should be in question form (Jeopardy style).</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">teams[ ] — team names</div><div class="civ">Find <code>var teams=[{name:'Team 1'...}]</code> in the code. Add or remove teams, and change names to match your class groups.</div></div>
          <div class="citem"><div class="cik">Daily Double</div><div class="civ">Add <code>dd:true</code> to any clue object to make it a Daily Double — the cell turns gold. Example: <code>{q:"...", a:"...", dd:true}</code></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="teacher-note">🎯 <strong>How to use in class:</strong> Teams take turns choosing a category and point value. Teacher clicks the cell, reads the clue, and students answer in question form ("What is...?"). Teacher reveals the answer, then awards points to the correct team. First to pick gets to answer.</div>
        <div class="claude-prompt">
          <div class="claude-prompt-label">📋 Ready-to-use Claude prompt — copy and paste this into Claude</div>
          <div class="claude-prompt-text" id="jj-prompt">Generate content for a Jeopardy EFL board game.

5 categories related to [your topic, e.g. grammar / vocabulary / British culture]. Level: [A2/B1/B2].

For each category, write 5 clues with increasing difficulty (100, 200, 300, 400, 500 points).

Format:
cats: ["Category 1","Category 2","Category 3","Category 4","Category 5"]

clues (5 arrays, one per category, each with 5 objects):
[
  [{q:"Clue 100",a:"What is answer?"},{q:"Clue 200",a:"What is answer?"},...],
  ...
]

