_\\n3. What was sealed with green wax? \\u2192 _______\\n4. What word was inside the envelope? \\u2192 ______\",\n      answer:\"MSED\",\n      hint:\"Read carefully: Monday, Scarlet, Envelope, Danger. First letters: M, S, E, D.\"\n    },\n    { id:\"ballroom\",name:\"Ballroom\",       icon:\"&#127928;\", color:\"#ec4899\", skill:\"Writing — Reported Speech\",\n      instruction:\"Three witnesses gave statements. Transform each DIRECT SPEECH sentence into REPORTED SPEECH. The KEY WORD is the main verb in your reported speech sentence. Take the FIRST LETTER of each key word to spell the 3-letter code.\",\n      task:\"1. Lady Ashton said: \\\"I saw the thief at midnight.\\\"\\n   \\u2192 Lady Ashton said (that) she _______ the thief at midnight.\\n   Key verb: _______\\n\\n2. The butler said: \\\"I will call the police immediately.\\\"\\n   \\u2192 The butler said (that) he _______ call the police.\\n   Key verb: _______\\n\\n3. The maid said: \\\"I have hidden the evidence in the attic.\\\"\\n   \\u2192 The maid said (that) she _______ hidden the evidence.\\n   Key verb: _______\",\n      answer:\"SWH\",\n      hint:\"Reported speech rules: see\\u2192saw, will\\u2192would, have hidden\\u2192had hidden. Key verbs: saw, would, had.\"\n    },\n    { id:\"cellar\",  name:\"Secret Cellar\",  icon:\"&#128273;\", color:\"#ef4444\", skill:\"Final Challenge — All Skills\",\n      instruction:\"You find The Shadow's codebook. Crack the FINAL CODE by solving this 4-part cipher. Write one letter per answer. Together they spell the secret code word (4 letters).\",\n      task:\"Part 1 \\u2014 Vocabulary:\\nA word meaning 'to escape from a place secretly' (starts with F, 4 letters)\\n\\u2192 First letter: _\\n\\nPart 2 \\u2014 Grammar:\\nThe tense used for future plans and arrangements (two words: present ___________)\\n\\u2192 First letter of second word: _\\n\\nPart 3 \\u2014 Reading:\\n'The artefact was hidden BENEATH the floor of the room where wine is stored.'\\nWhat room? \